      <!-- Ingredient Deep-Dive -->
      <h2>Key Ingredients for Hair Growth</h2>

      <div class="info-cards">
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-card-ico">B7</div>
          <h4>Biotin (Vitamin B7)</h4>
          <p>Cornerstone of every hair supplement. Cofactor for carboxylase enzymes that synthesize keratin. Subclinical deficiency is more common than recognized — especially in pregnant women, those on anticonvulsants/antibiotics, and people with GI conditions. Clinical dose: 2,500-5,000 mcg/day.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-card-ico">Col</div>
          <h4>Collagen (Marine & Bovine)</h4>
          <p>Provides proline, glycine, and hydroxyproline to produce keratin and maintain the dermal layer around follicles. Marine collagen has a lower molecular weight than bovine, potentially improving absorption. Viviscal's AminoMar is the most clinically studied marine collagen for hair.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-card-ico">SP</div>
          <h4>Saw Palmetto</h4>
          <p>Natural 5-alpha-reductase inhibitor that reduces conversion of testosterone to DHT — the androgen responsible for follicle miniaturization in pattern hair loss. Found in both Nutrafol and Hims formulas. Fewer side effects than finasteride.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-card-ico">KR</div>
          <h4>Keratin (Cynatine HNS)</h4>
          <p>Solubilized keratin peptides provide the exact amino acids found in hair structure. A 90-day RCT published in <em>Scientific Reports</em> showed significant improvements in hair strength, brightness, and reduced shedding compared to placebo. Increasingly used in premium gummy formulas alongside biotin.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="callout">Collagen supplementation improved overall skin and hair quality markers in the majority of studies examined.<cite>— International Journal of Dermatology, 2020</cite></div>

